for performance and future features, and are now compatible with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" property wrapper."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of."}]},{"text":"Store internals rewrite","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test your application after upgrading."}]},{"text":"StateObject compatibility","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"StateObject-compatibility"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One important difference between "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is that "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"eager, while "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s is lazy. Because of this, if you initialize a root "},{"code":"Store","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to be held"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", stores will be initialized (and immediately discarded) whenever the parent view’s body"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is computed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To avoid the creation of these stores, one can now assign the store to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", instead:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct FeatureView: View {","  @StateObject var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  init() {","    _store = StateObject(","      \/\/ This expression is only evaluated the first time the parent view is computed.","      wrappedValue: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","        Feature()","      }","    )","  }","","  var body: some View { \/* ... *\/ }","}"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The store’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"ObservableObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformance does not have any impact on the actual","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"observability of the store. You should continue to rely on the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ObservableState()","type":"reference"},{"text":" macro for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"observation.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important"}]